Swanlake draws on prior work in the agent-security research space. The
following projects and publications informed the design; Swanlake is not
derived from their source code but acknowledges their influence on the
problem framing.

- OWASP Top 10 for Large Language Model Applications (2025 edition)
  https://genai.owasp.org/llm-top-10/
- Model Context Protocol specification, incremental-scope authorization
  https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification/draft/basic/authorization
- Anthropic — "Mitigating the risk of prompt injections in browser use" (2025)
  https://www.anthropic.com/news/prompt-injection-defenses
- DeepMind — "AI Agent Traps" taxonomy (SSRN 6372438, March 2026)
- Academic prompt-injection and RAG-poisoning literature, 2023–2026.
  See THREAT-MODEL.md for the citation list.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Third-party dependencies declared in each package's metadata file.
Swanlake's reference implementations are stdlib-only where possible to
minimize the dependency surface.
